channel.title: Adding Objects
channel.description: Okay I am using Devo7 Source and I'm not sure if its even possible to add objects to this source. I've tried everything, I've tried adding to the objects.cfg, I've tried adding through Client.Java in every way, shape, and form. Is there any other possible way to add objects? If anyone knows it would help alot. Thank you.

item.title: Adding Objects
item.dc:creator: @Torax1 Torax™
item.description:
@Torax1 wrote:

If you knew java, you would know that that DOES NOT mean that all of your files have compiled successfully. Read what it says.

Some input files use or override a deprecated AIP.

They compiled, but obviously some of them override other files.

Read full topic

[quote=“Torax™, post:5, topic:261843”]Well this might be the problem. When I compile I always get this message.

Note: Some input files use or override a deprecated AIP.
Note: Recompile with -Xlint:deprecation for details.
Files Compiled Successfully!

You see it compiles but I’m afraid it might not have compiled my objects.
Is there any way to fix this, and I dont know what Xlint is or how to use it.[/quote]
That message means that your ALL your files have compiled correctly.
